    narr:Metrics_TonyScarletCall_20260331 a narr:StyleMetrics ;
      skos:broader narr:StyleMetrics ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_TonyScarletCall_20260331 ;
      skos:note "Live call transcript register. Both speakers use conversational, filler-heavy speech with run-on sentences. Scarlet's quoted speech is longer and more analytical (~28 words avg); Tony's is shorter and more declarative (~14 words avg). Active voice dominant in both speakers. Jargon density low — Lean Startup, product market fit, token consumption are the only domain terms. Profanity used by Scarlet as rhetorical intensifier at conviction peaks. Antithesis-heavy structure (execution vs. strategy, humans-first vs. features-first, free vs. paid)." ;
